## Summary: ASG Testing Patterns Exploration

I've thoroughly explored the ASG testing codebase and can provide you with a comprehensive overview of the testing patterns. Here's what I found:

### 1. **UNIT TEST STRUCTURE** (src/test/java/com/grl/component/)

**Key Files:**
- `/home/mike/grl/ASG/src/test/java/com/grl/component/mapper/TaxonomyPropertyMapperTest.java`
- `/home/mike/grl/ASG/src/test/java/com/grl/component/mapper/DataPropertyMapperTest.java`
- `/home/mike/grl/ASG/src/test/java/com/grl/component/schema/SchemaVisitorTest.java`

**Patterns Used:**

1. **JUnit 5 with Nested Test Classes**
   - Uses `@BeforeEach` for setup
   - Organizes tests with `@Nested` classes (logical grouping)
   - Example from `TaxonomyPropertyMapperTest`:
     ```java
     @Nested
     class BasicSchemaGeneration {
       @Test
       void testSingleEnumValueCreatesStringSchemaWithEnum() { ... }
     }

     @Nested
     class ArrayGeneration {
       @Test
       void testSomeValuesFromRestrictionCreatesArraySchema() { ... }
     }
     ```

2. **Test Setup Pattern**
   ```java
   @BeforeEach
   void setUp() throws OWLOntologyCreationException {
     manager = OWLManager.createOWLOntologyManager();
     df = manager.getOWLDataFactory();
     ontology = manager.createOntology(IRI.create(TEST_NS));
     config = new YamlConfig();
     // Create context with test data
     context = new MappingContext(...);
   }
   ```

3. **Direct Mapper Testing**
   - Instantiate mapper with test data directly
   - Example:
     ```java
     TaxonomyPropertyMapper mapper = new TaxonomyPropertyMapper(
         context, "status", "Status description", "Status Label",
         List.of("Active"), Collections.emptySet());
     Schema<?> schema = mapper.getTaxonomySchemaObject();
     ```

4. **Assertion Patterns**
   - `assertInstanceOf()` for type checking
   - `assertEquals()` for values
   - `assertTrue()`/`assertFalse()` for conditions
   - Collections assertions: `contains()`, `size()`, `isEmpty()`

**Nested Test Organization for TaxonomyPropertyMapperTest:**
- `BasicSchemaGeneration` - Schema creation tests
- `ArrayGeneration` - Array vs singular tests
- `RequirednessHandling` - Required field tests
- `RestrictionApplication` - Restriction mapping tests
- `ArrayMetadata` - Array property tests
- `NullRestrictions` - Edge cases

---

### 2. **INTEGRATION TEST STRUCTURE** (src/test/java/regression/features/)

**Key Files:**
- `/home/mike/grl/ASG/src/test/java/regression/features/properties/TaxonomyPropertyIT.java`
- `/home/mike/grl/ASG/src/test/java/regression/features/restrictions/CardinalityRestrictionsIT.java`
- `/home/mike/grl/ASG/src/test/java/regression/features/restrictions/ValueRestrictionsIT.java`

**Pattern: Full Pipeline Testing**

1. **Single-Method Setup with Caching**
   ```java
   private static ReadContext spec;

   @BeforeAll
   static void setup() {
     spec = TestUtil.getGeneratedSpec(
         TestUtil.asFilePath(TaxonomyPropertyIT.class, 
                            "/regression/configs/config_taxonomy.yaml"));
   }
   ```

2. **JSONPath-based Assertions**
   - Uses `com.jayway.jsonpath.ReadContext` to query generated OpenAPI spec
   - Example:
     ```java
     List<String> enumValues = spec.read(
         "$.components.schemas.TaxonomyTest.properties.Status.items.enum", 
         List.class);
     assertTrue(enumValues.contains("Active"));
     ```

3. **Test Organization**
   - Each method tests one specific behavior
   - No nesting (flat structure, unlike unit tests)
   - Tests cover multiple aspects: types, arrays, required fields, structure

4. **Common Assertion Patterns**
   ```java
   // Type checks
   assertEquals("array", spec.read("$.components.schemas.TaxonomyTest.properties.Status.type"));

   // Array properties
   assertEquals(1, spec.read("$.components.schemas.TaxonomyTest.properties.Status.minItems", Integer.class));

   // Required fields
   List<String> required = spec.read("$.components.schemas.TaxonomyTest.required", List.class);
   assertTrue(required.contains("Status"));

   // Schema structure
   assertEquals("object", spec.read("$.components.schemas.TaxonomyTest.type"));
   assertEquals("Taxonomy Test", spec.read("$.components.schemas.TaxonomyTest.title"));
   ```

---

### 3. **TEST ONTOLOGY SETUP**

**Location:** `/home/mike/grl/ASG/src/test/resources/regression/ontologies/`

**Taxonomy Test Ontology** (`taxonomy-test.owl`):
```xml
<!-- Taxonomy Class with Named Individuals -->
<owl:Class rdf:about="https://example.com/taxonomy/Status">
    <skos:prefLabel>Status</skos:prefLabel>
</owl:Class>

<!-- Individuals (enum values) -->
<owl:NamedIndividual rdf:about="https://example.com/taxonomy/StatusActive">
    <rdf:type rdf:resource="https://example.com/taxonomy/Status"/>
    <skos:prefLabel>Active</skos:prefLabel>
</owl:NamedIndividual>

<!-- Object Property pointing to Taxonomy -->
<owl:ObjectProperty rdf:about="https://example.com/taxonomy/hasStatus"/>

<!-- Resource with taxonomy restriction -->
<owl:Class rdf:about="https://example.com/taxonomy/TaxonomyTest">
    <rdfs:subClassOf rdf:nodeID="hasStatusRestr"/>
</owl:Class>

<!-- Restriction: someValuesFrom Status -->
<owl:Restriction rdf:nodeID="hasStatusRestr">
    <owl:onProperty rdf:resource="https://example.com/taxonomy/hasStatus"/>
    <owl:someValuesFrom rdf:resource="https://example.com/taxonomy/Status"/>
</owl:Restriction>
```

**Configuration Pattern** (`config_taxonomy.yaml`):
```yaml
extends: ../config_base.yaml
ontologies:
  - ${configDir}/../ontologies/taxonomy-test.owl
name: taxonomy_test
rootClass: https://example.com/taxonomy/TaxonomyTestAPIV1.0
templates:
  openapi:
    openapi: 3.1.0
    info:
      description: Taxonomy Test API
      title: Taxonomy Test
      version: 1.0.0
```

**Base Configuration** (`config_base.yaml`):
```yaml
namespaceMappings:
  - "!http://www.w3.org/2002/07/owl#.*"
  - "!http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#.*"
  - '.*'
enforceRequiredness: True
outputDir: ${configDir}/../../test-output
```

---

### 4. **TEST UTILITY HELPERS**

**TestUtil Class** (`/home/mike/grl/ASG/src/test/java/com/grl/TestUtil.java`):

```java
// Load config file from resources
public static Path asFilePath(Class<?> cls, String resourceName)

// Generate spec and return parsed JSON (with caching)
public static ReadContext getGeneratedSpec(Path configPath)

// Copy resource to temp file
public static Path copyToRealFile(Class<?> cls, String resourceName)

// Internal generation method
public static DocumentContext generate(Path configPath)
```

**Usage in Integration Tests:**
```java
spec = TestUtil.getGeneratedSpec(
    TestUtil.asFilePath(TaxonomyPropertyIT.class, 
                       "/regression/configs/config_taxonomy.yaml"));
```

---

### 5. **TAXONOMY/ENUM HANDLING EXAMPLES**

**Unit Test Pattern** (TaxonomyPropertyMapperTest):
```java
@Test
void testMultipleEnumValuesCreateStringSchemaWithEnumList() {
  TaxonomyPropertyMapper mapper = new TaxonomyPropertyMapper(
      context, "status", "Status description", "Status Label",
      List.of("Active", "Inactive", "Pending"), Collections.emptySet());

  Schema<?> schema = mapper.getTaxonomySchemaObject();

  assertInstanceOf(StringSchema.class, schema);
  StringSchema stringSchema = (StringSchema) schema;
  assertNotNull(stringSchema.getEnum());
  assertEquals(3, stringSchema.getEnum().size());
  assertTrue(stringSchema.getEnum().contains("Active"));
  assertTrue(stringSchema.getEnum().contains("Inactive"));
  assertTrue(stringSchema.getEnum().contains("Pending"));
}
```

**Integration Test Pattern** (TaxonomyPropertyIT):
```java
@Test
void statusTaxonomyCreatesEnumFromIndividuals() {
  assertNotNull(spec.read("$.components.schemas.TaxonomyTest.properties.Status"));

  List<String> enumValues = spec.read(
      "$.components.schemas.TaxonomyTest.properties.Status.items.enum", 
      List.class);

  assertNotNull(enumValues, "Status should have enum values");
  assertTrue(enumValues.contains("Active"));
  assertTrue(enumValues.contains("Inactive"));
  assertTrue(enumValues.contains("Pending"));
}

@Test
void taxonomyPropertyIsArrayType() {
  assertEquals("array", 
      spec.read("$.components.schemas.TaxonomyTest.properties.Status.type"));
  assertEquals("array", 
      spec.read("$.components.schemas.TaxonomyTest.properties.Priority.type"));
}

@Test
void taxonomyPropertiesAreRequired() {
  List<String> required = spec.read(
      "$.components.schemas.TaxonomyTest.required", List.class);
  assertTrue(required.contains("Status"), "Status should be required");
  assertTrue(required.contains("Priority"), "Priority should be required");
}
```

---

### 6. **KEY PATTERNS FOR NEW TAXONOMY TESTS**

**For Unit Tests (focusing on mapper behavior):**
1. Setup ontology manager, data factory, context in `@BeforeEach`
2. Use `@Nested` classes to organize test groups
3. Create mapper instances directly with test data
4. Assert on schema properties: type, enum, required, minItems/maxItems
5. Test edge cases: null restrictions, empty enums, etc.

**For Integration Tests (focusing on full pipeline):**
1. Create OWL ontology with:
   - Taxonomy class (e.g., `Status`)
   - Named individuals as enum values
   - Object property pointing to taxonomy class
   - Resource class with `someValuesFrom` restriction
2. Create YAML config extending `config_base.yaml`
3. Use `TestUtil.getGeneratedSpec()` in `@BeforeAll` static method
4. Query generated spec with JSONPath assertions
5. Test: array type, enum values, required fields, structure

**Assertion Approach:**
- Unit: Direct schema object assertions
- Integration: JSONPath queries on final OpenAPI spec

---

All file paths are absolute and ready for reference in your test development!

